speaker: ADAM
text: Dear master, I can go no further. O, I die for

speaker: ADAM
text: food. Here lie I down and measure out my grave.

speaker: ORLANDO
text: Why, how now, Adam? No greater heart in

speaker: ORLANDO
text: thee? Live a little, comfort a little, cheer thyself a

speaker: ORLANDO
text: little. If this uncouth forest yield anything savage, I

speaker: ORLANDO
text: will either be food for it or bring it for food to thee.

speaker: ORLANDO
text: Thy conceit is nearer death than thy powers. For my

speaker: ORLANDO
text: sake, be comfortable. Hold death awhile at the

speaker: ORLANDO
text: arm’s end. I will here be with thee presently, and if

speaker: ORLANDO
text: I bring thee not something to eat, I will give thee

speaker: ORLANDO
text: leave to die. But if thou diest before I come, thou art

speaker: ORLANDO
text: a mocker of my labor. Well said. Thou look’st

speaker: ORLANDO
text: cheerly, and I’ll be with thee quickly. Yet thou liest

speaker: ORLANDO
text: in the bleak air. Come, I will bear thee to some

speaker: ORLANDO
text: shelter, and thou shalt not die for lack of a dinner if

speaker: ORLANDO
text: there live anything in this desert. Cheerly, good
